sentences: Ralf Weikert (born 10 November 1940) is an Austrian conductor, especially of operas by Mozart and Rossini.
Weikert was from 1971 a regular conductor at the Salzburg Festival.
From 1981 to 1984, he was Chefdirigent of the Mozarteum Orchestra Salzburg.
From 1983 to 1992, he was Musikdirektor at  the Opernhaus Zürich.
He has been a professor of conducting at the Musikhochschule Luzern from 2008.
